GLP_LO coupling / y-accumulator sign correction example
=========================================================

Problem
-------
Minimize  -x1 - y1
Subject to
  x1 <= 5         (sub1 constraint)
  y1 <= 5         (sub2 constraint)
  x1 + y1 >= 3    (coupling constraint, GLP_LO)
  x1, y1 >= 0

Known optimal
-------------
x1 = 5, y1 = 5
Objective = -(5 + 5) = -10

Code path exercised
-------------------
The ">=" (GLP_LO) coupling constraint exercises two previously untested
code paths:

1. dw_main.c GLP_LO branch: converts the row to GLP_FX by adding a slack
   variable (sl_i) and an artificial variable (y_i) for Phase I.

2. phase_1_iteration() first-run sign correction: when the y-accumulator
   contributions from the initial lambda columns already exceed the lower
   bound of the coupling row (i.e. x1+y1 > 3 from the initial sub-optimal
   extreme points), the condition

       glp_get_row_lb(master_lp, i) - y_accumulators[i] < 0.0

   triggers, and the y_i artificial variable's coefficient is flipped to
   -1.0 so that Phase I drives y_i to zero from the correct direction.
   This is the "neg_y" path named in the code comment.
